// The Weiser Concise Guide to Alchemy

== The Weiser Concise Guide to Alchemy
_by Brian Cotnoir_

=== Modern Principles
- *Safety as Foundation:* Proper ventilation, glassware integrity, and "Presence" in the lab.
- *The Microcosm:* The practitioner's inner state is the "Inner Lab" that mirrors the outer work.
- *The Language of Symbols:* Understanding alchemical emblems not as puzzles, but as resonant maps of consciousness.

#v(2em)

= Classical Authorities

== Turba Philosophorum (The Assembly of the Sages)
- *Theme:* A series of "debates" between Greek philosophers on the nature of the Prime Matter.
- *Core Insight:* All elements are transmutable because they all arise from a single, chaotic substance (The Abyss).

== Aphorismi Urbigerus
- *Theme:* 101 aphorisms providing the rules for the preparation of the Grand Elixir.
- *Core Insight:* Detailed focus on the *Circulation* and the *Multiplication* of the Stone's power.

== Isaac Hollandus & Basil Valentine
- *Hollandus:* Master of the "Vegetable Work" and the use of urine/vinegar as solvents.
- *Valentine:* The "Triumphal Chariot of Antimony." Established the mineral's medicinal supremacy and the use of the "Star Regulus."